column5: Looking for info on this rd up to windigo lake,fishing along this rd,rd condition
Now I know you can help outwas going to end of rd (windigo) and fish back to town (10 days) septany info would help
The last time I went up that road, there was a sign about 5 km north of Pickle Lake by the last house on the left, it read:"You are now leaving civilization"Hope this helps

I'd like to learn more about the road too. I've been going to a camp near Pickle Lake for over 10 years, but the road north is calling. A friend was up to Windigo about 30 years back and we've been talking about taking the trip again for several years now.

I met Gary and his wife Amelia back in 02--they left shortly after that. Bought gas at Windigo from Gary, had to hook jumper cables to our battery to operate the gas pump. Very interesting couple and interest place they had there.
So any new news on fishing the North rd and Behrens lake
